                "text": "Well I think most Smalltalk implementations will not regard there image as an Object. The VM is probably often the element responsible for reading the image and creating the actual Objects (including Class, CompiledMethod, Context, etc) and continue execution where it left of when being saved.\n"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "That said, it would definitely be possible to see it as an Object. A Smalltalk implementation could even run (simulate?) the environment inside a supplied image. Do remember that things like garbage collection are often (must often) be done by the VM. So simulation is not trivial and might require quite a few extra features in the ‘receiving’ Smalltalk image. HTH"
